Class JSONMap

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>

        • java.util.LinkedHashMap<String,Object>
          • com.fortify.util.rest.json.JSONMap
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, Map<String,Object>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ArcherAuthData

    public class JSONMap
extends LinkedHashMap<String,Object>
    This class represents JSON objects as a standard Java Map, adding some JSON-related utility methods.
    Author:
    Ruud Senden

    Serialized Form

      • putPath

        public void putPath(String path,
                    Object value)
        Add a value to this JSONMap under the given property path. This will create the property path if it does not yet exist.
        Parameters:
        path - to be added to this JSONMap
        value - to be stored under the given path

      • putPath

        public void putPath(String path,
                    Object value,
                    boolean ignoreNullOrEmptyValues)
        Add a value to this JSONMap under the given property path. This will create the property path if it does not yet exist. Depending on the ignoreNullOrEmptyValues parameter, values that are null, blank strings, or empty collections or arrays, will be ignored.
        Parameters:
        path - to be added to this JSONMap
        value - to be stored under the given path
        ignoreNullOrEmptyValues - Don't add null or empty value if set to true
